## **2: Data Process**

### Calculate HICDD

```{r, echo = TRUE, message = FALSE, warning = FALSE}

HICDD <- calculateHICDD(2016:2020)
saveRDS(HICDD, file.path(data_path, "HICDD.rds"))

```

### Clean building related datasets

```{r, echo = TRUE, message = FALSE, warning = FALSE}
#Interpolate and save GPW data
GPW_process()

#Filter buildings without any people (This takes five minutes)
Building_filter()

# Create mapping of buildings, zctas and communities (This takes about 10 hours)
Building_Energy() # This generates a file about 3GB.

```

### Impute energy data with adjusted dasymetric method

```{r, echo = TRUE, message = FALSE, warning = FALSE}
# Perform Adjusted Dasymetric imputation ()
#MSE indicates MSE values across all combinations of height scores.
#The imputed energy data will be saved as final_energy_data.rds, which can be found at /Data
MSE <- Adjusted_Dasymetric()

print(MSE)
```

